      <body>I see two advantages to this approach:

1. It's somewhat drier when you have a gem that's used in more than one environment

2. DHH's approach requires you to run rake gem:install for each environment to be sure you've got everything; it would be nice to be able to run it once across all environments</body>
      <body-html>&lt;div&gt;&lt;p&gt;I see two advantages to this approach:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ol&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;It's somewhat drier when you have a gem that's used in more than
one environment&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;DHH's approach requires you to run rake gem:install for each
environment to be sure you've got everything; it would be nice to
be able to run it once across all environments&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ol&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</body-html>
